{
  "texts": [
    "To fully understand how data features relate to model performance and to determine the best settings for ML-based systematic reviews in education and educational psychology, it is crucial to evaluate these learning algorithms on a broader set of systematic reviews from the education and educational psychology research fields.",
    "The performance of heuristic stopping criteria is a second aspect of ML-based tools with scarce and mixed evidence.",
    "For example, Wallace et al. (2010) found that using a time-based approach in which reviewers classified 50% of all records in a database resulted in a 100% recall.",
    "In contrast, Callaghan and Müller-Hansen (2020) found that data-driven approaches could not find 95% of all relevant records in 39% of the 20 systematic reviews analyzed.",
    "The results of these simulation studies represent an important source of information on the reliability of heuristic stopping criteria."
  ]
}